Motherboard

- Skeleton and nervous system, connecting everything together  
- Rear I/O ports  
  - Connect keyboard, mice, monitors, USB devices  
- CPU Socket  
  - Connects the CPU (processer)  
- PCI XS Slot  
  - Connects the Graphics & Network card  
- DIMM  
  - Connects RAM modules  
- SATA ports  
  - SSD/HDD and SATA cables

CPU

- Brain of the computer, constantly executing instructions

RAM

- Short-term memory \- fast but temporary

SSH/HDD

- Storage devices for long-term data retention

Network adapters

- Allow a computer to communicate with other systems

PSU

- Power Supply Unit

Graphics Card

- Processes visuals for your monitor

Boot Sequence

- Pressing power button  
  - Sends signal to PSU to let power through  
- Firmware Starts  
  - UEFI firmware initialized and coordinates components  
- POST (power on self test)  
  - UEFI runs POST to check required hardware is present/configured/working  
- Select Boot device  
  - UEFI follows priority lest to determine which device to boot from  
- Initialize bootloader  
  - Bootloader loads OS into RAM. UEFI gives control to the OS
